# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Fairway Fantasy — environment template
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to ``.env.local`` and fill in real values.
# ``.env.local`` is gitignored — never commit it.
#
# Three modes:
#
# 1. PREVIEW THE LANDING PAGE ONLY (no auth, no DB):
#    Leave Supabase vars empty. Run ``npm run dev``. The landing page
#    at http://localhost:3000/ renders. Auth-gated pages will surface
#    a clear error. ``npm run build`` succeeds — every auth-gated
#    route is now `dynamic = 'force-dynamic'`.
#
# 2. FULL DEV MODE (real Supabase Cloud project):
#    Create a free project at https://supabase.com, run
#    ``supabase/schema.sql`` in the SQL editor, then fill in the
#    URL/keys below. ``npm run build`` and ``npm run dev`` both work.
#
# 3. LAN PROD (192.168.1.160):
#    Same vars as #2 but with NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL pointed at the LAN
#    URL. See DEPLOYMENT.md for the full systemd / nginx / Postgres
#    walkthrough.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Database ──
# kysely connects directly via pg. Two valid sources:
#
# Phase 2/3 (still on Supabase Cloud — direct pg connection):
#   Project Settings → Database → "Connection string" → URI tab.
#   Use port 5432 (session mode), not 6543 (transaction-pooled mode):
#     postgresql://postgres:PASSWORD@db.xxx.supabase.co:5432/postgres
#
# Phase 5+ (local Postgres on 192.168.1.160):
#   Stand up via infra/postgres/docker-compose.yml. Default user:
#     postgresql://fairway:PASSWORD@127.0.0.1:5432/fairway
#
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://fairway:replace-me@127.0.0.1:5432/fairway

# ── Supabase project (auth flow only — Phase-4 deletes this) ──
# Until Phase 4 swaps in NextAuth Credentials, the browser-side
# auth flow (signin/signup/Nav signOut) still uses the Supabase
# anon client. Once Phase 4 lands, these can be removed entirely.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.your-anon-key

# ── Cron secret ──
# Used by /api/sync-scores and /api/admin/reminders for systemd timer
# server-to-server auth. NOT prefixed with NEXT_PUBLIC_ — never
# bundled into client JS. Generate with `openssl rand -hex 32`.
CRON_SECRET=replace-with-a-random-string

# ── Public site URL ──
# Used to build absolute invite URLs and reminder pickUrls.
# - Local dev:       http://localhost:3000
# - LAN prod:        http://192.168.1.160:3000  (or whatever port nginx listens on)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=http://localhost:3000

# ── Reminders (P9): live mode toggle ──
# Default: not set. Reminders are logged to console + reminder_log
# only — no real emails/SMS/push are sent.
# Set REMINDERS_LIVE=true ONLY after wiring a ChannelDriver in
# `src/lib/notifier.ts` (e.g. SMTP config below). Until then, leave
# this empty so we can't accidentally send anything.
# REMINDERS_LIVE=true

# ── (Future) SMTP for email reminders ──
# Not used today — the email driver is the placeholder console driver.
# When you wire a real SMTP driver, add these:
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.example.com
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_USER=
# SMTP_PASSWORD=
# SMTP_FROM="Fairway Fantasy <noreply@fairway.local>"

# ── (Future) Twilio / push provider ──
# Same pattern — placeholder until a real driver is registered.
# TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=
# TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=
# TWILIO_FROM=+15551234567

# ── DataGolf API key (currently unused) ──
# README references this but datagolf.ts now sources rankings from
# ESPN's free API instead. Leave blank.
# DATAGOLF_API_KEY=
